---
/**
 * Plans feature showcase. Angle: agents drift without structure.
 * Plans eliminate Plan Drift, Focus Drift, and Execution Hallucination
 * by giving the agent an explicit task list to execute within.
 *
 * This is the system-centric architecture made concrete: the plan
 * lives outside the model, survives sessions, and is shared across
 * agents. The model executes — it doesn't reconstruct.
 */
---

<section class="section plans">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="eyebrow">
			<span class="eyebrow-text">PLANS //</span>
		</div>
		<h2 class="section-title">Agents drift. Plans don't.</h2>
		<p class="section-lede">
			Without structure, an agent re-reasons its position on every
			turn — re-reading prior output, reconstructing intent, deciding
			what to do next. That's plan drift, and you pay for every token
			of it. Plans give the agent an external task list to execute
			within. It picks up exactly where work left off.
		</p>

		<div class="plans-layout">
			<div class="plans-copy">
				<div class="feature-row">
					<div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">▸</div>
					<div>
						<h3>No re-reasoning between sessions</h3>
						<p>
							A plan persists in the state graph. When an agent
							resumes — tomorrow, or after a context switch — it calls
							<code>plan_next</code> and gets exactly what to do next.
							No context reconstruction. No token overhead.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="feature-row">
					<div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">▸</div>
					<div>
						<h3>Shared across agents and tools</h3>
						<p>
							Plans live on branches, not in a session. Claude Code,
							Cursor, and a Python script can all work from the same
							plan simultaneously — each picking up the next available
							task with <code>plan_next(assigned_to="me")</code>.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="feature-row">
					<div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">▸</div>
					<div>
						<h3>Proof-of-work on every task</h3>
						<p>
							Closing a task requires a proof: a commit SHA, a file
							path, or a test. No execution hallucination — no agent
							marking work done that wasn't. The plan is an audit
							trail as well as a task list.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="plans-terminal">
				<div class="terminal-bar">
					<span class="dot dot-red"></span>
					<span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
					<span class="dot dot-green"></span>
					<span class="terminal-title">ctx plan show auth-refactor</span>
				</div>
				<pre class="terminal-body"><code><span class="t-dim">plan:</span>  <span class="t-white">auth-refactor</span>  <span class="t-dim">branch: main</span>
<span class="t-dim">─────────────────────────────────────────</span>

  <span class="t-done">✓</span>  <span class="t-dim">Audit existing JWT middleware</span>
  <span class="t-done">✓</span>  <span class="t-dim">Document token expiry edge cases</span>
  <span class="t-active">▸</span>  <span class="t-white">Replace JWT middleware</span>  <span class="t-badge">in_progress</span>
  <span class="t-pending">○</span>  <span class="t-dim">Update integration tests</span>
  <span class="t-pending">○</span>  <span class="t-dim">Update docs/AUTH.md</span>

<span class="t-dim">─────────────────────────────────────────</span>
<span class="t-dim">2 done · 1 in progress · 2 pending</span>

<span class="t-prompt">$</span> ctx plan next
<span class="t-dim">→</span> <span class="t-white">Replace JWT middleware</span>
  <span class="t-dim">blocked_by: [] · assigned_to: claude-code</span></code></pre>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="plans-link">
			<a href="/reference/cli/#plans">See the full plans CLI reference →</a>
		</p>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.plans {
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse 60% 40% at 80% 50%,
				rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.05),
				transparent 60%
			),
			var(--ctx-bg);
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-lo);
	}

	.eyebrow {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.08);
		border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.28);
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.plans-layout {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 3rem;
		align-items: start;
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
	}

	.feature-row {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
	}

	.feature-row:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.feature-icon {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		flex-shrink: 0;
		margin-top: 0.2rem;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.feature-row h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: #ffffff;
		margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.feature-row p {
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.feature-row p code {
		background: #0a0a0a;
		padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-sm);
		font-size: 0.85em;
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	/* Terminal widget */
	.plans-terminal {
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		overflow: hidden;
		background: #050505;
	}

	.terminal-bar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.4rem;
		padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-lo);
	}

	.dot {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 50%;
	}

	.dot-red    { background: #ef4444; opacity: 0.7; }
	.dot-yellow { background: #f59e0b; opacity: 0.7; }
	.dot-green  { background: #22c55e; opacity: 0.7; }

	.terminal-title {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		margin-left: 0.25rem;
	}

	.terminal-body {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}

	.terminal-body code {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.t-white   { color: #ffffff; }
	.t-dim     { color: var(--ctx-text-faint); }
	.t-done    { color: var(--ctx-success); }
	.t-active  { color: var(--ctx-success); font-weight: 700; }
	.t-pending { color: var(--ctx-text-faint); }
	.t-prompt  { color: var(--ctx-success); }

	.t-badge {
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
		background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.12);
		border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3);
		border-radius: 999px;
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.plans-link {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		font-size: 0.88rem;
	}

	.plans-link a {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
	}

	@media (max-width: 860px) {
		.plans-layout {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
